            <title>[SPARK-6133] SparkContext#stop is not idempotent</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-6133</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If we call sc.stop() twice, the listener bus will attempt to log an event after stop() is called, resulting in a scary error message. This happens if Spark calls sc.stop() internally (it does this on certain error conditions) and the application code calls it again, for instance.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
